  "info": {
    "title": "API Reference",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "description": "## Web API\nRetrieve behavioral insights, candidate analytics, and team performance data.\n\nThe OAD.ai Web API enables the creation of applications that can access organizational analytics, manage teams and candidates, and monitor credit usage — all through secure, token-based endpoints.\n\n## Getting Started\n\n**Base URL**  \n```\nhttps://app.oad.ai/api/app/v1/oad\n```\n\n## Authentication\nAll requests require Bearer Token authorization.  \nInclude your token in the `Authorization` header of each request:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <your_api_token>\n```\n\nRequests without a valid token will return `401 Unauthorized`.\n\n\n## Obtaining an API Token\n- API tokens can be generated from your OAD.ai admin dashboard under **Settings → Integration → Generate Token**. \n- Tokens are tied to your organization account and must be kept secure.\n\n## Example Request\n```\ncurl -X GET \"https://app.oad.ai/api/app/v1/oadteam/info\" \\\n-H \"Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.example_signature\"\n```\n\n ## Rate Limits\n- Each API key allows **60 requests per minute** per organization.  \n- Exceeding this limit will result in a `429 Too Many Requests` error.  \n- Rate-limit details are returned in response headers:\n- Use efficient caching and batch requests to stay within the rate window."
  },
